{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 15:34:36.522595", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission summary:\n- Anomaly detected: Yes\n- Faulty devices: web_server_3, web_server_0, web_server_1, web_server_2\n- Root cause(s): sender_application_delay, sender_resource_contention\n\nRationale:\n- All web servers have Apache inactive and are serving HTTP via a Python BaseHTTP server. On web_server_3, the single-threaded server returns a very large payload and frequently blocks, causing HTTP timeouts despite TCP connectivity. This matches sender-side application delay and resource contention rather than any network/L3 issue.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2295, "output_tokens": 118, "total_tokens": 2413, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 2176}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
